    "Beginning in 1874, Clarke accepted various foreign assignments as supervising architect to the crown, most notably Tehran.": [],
    "In 1876, Clarke traveled to Turkey, Syria, and Greece and in 1879 to Spain, Italy, and Germany buying artifacts for the Museum.": [],
    "Commissions to design architecture in the Indian style resulted in the Indian hall at Elvedon, Suffolk, 1899 with the architect William Young.": [
