    "In 1905 Clarke hired <a href=\"/robinsone\">Edward Robinson</a>, the recently-resigned director of the Museum of Fine Arts, Boston, to be his assistant director.": [],
    "Clarke's physical and perhaps emotional health declined.": [],
    "He returned to England on a leave of absence in 1909 and resigned his as director in 1910.": [],
    "Robinson succeeded him as director.": [],
